experiments_run.name: Genetic Algorithm
experiments_run.notes: GA maintains diverse population with crossover and mutation. Initial population includes baseline, perturbed baselines, and random configs. Baseline is always the best in the population - crossover/mutation cannot find better solutions.

analysis.crossover_effect: Combining trees from different solutions creates overlaps that need fixing
analysis.mutation_effect: Small mutations don't improve, large mutations create overlaps
analysis.conclusion: GA cannot escape the local optimum because: 1) Random configs are much worse than baseline, 2) Crossover creates invalid solutions, 3) Mutations don't find better configurations

conclusion: The baseline is at a TRUE local optimum that even GA cannot escape. All approaches (SA, fractional translation, random restart, constructive, ensemble, Numba SA, GA) have failed to find improvements. The baseline was created by sophisticated C++ optimization with millions of iterations. Without access to external data sources that found different local optima, we cannot improve on the baseline.
